   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Help Cocoa for Peace. Colombia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">230 men, women and complete cocoa growers families located in the North of Tolima Colombia, subsist from the production of cocoa. Cocoa for peace emerges as a subsistence mechanism for farm families who also find a way of social and economic transformation of a territory historically marked by violence. The farmers was victimized by various scourges such as drug trafficking, violence, sexual and labor exploitation against women and children by guerrillas and armed groups outside the law.</narrative>
  </description>
